m_q.target_metric: Compare finishing positions to determine who came in earlier between Tony Maggs and Jo Siffert
filters: Driver equals 'Tony Maggs' OR Driver equals 'Jo Siffert'
sub_questions: What is the 'Pos' value for Tony Maggs?
What is the 'Pos' value for Jo Siffert?
Which driver has the lower 'Pos' value (earlier finish)?

unit_annotations.Time/Retired: time difference from winner or reason for retirement

format_notes: Pos column is Int64 with nullable values for drivers who did not finish (DNF)
Time/Retired column contains either time differences (e.g., '+ 22.6 s') or laps completed (e.g., '72 laps') or retirement reasons (e.g., 'Engine (66 laps)')
Rows without Pos values indicate drivers who did not complete the race

constraints: Both Tony Maggs and Jo Siffert must exist in the Driver column
Pos values determine finishing order where lower values indicate earlier (better) finish
Null Pos values indicate did not finish (DNF) which is ranked after all finishers
output_format_requirements: Return the name of the driver who came in earlier (had lower Pos value)
If one driver has a Pos value and the other does not, the one with Pos value came in earlier
